SETUP INSTRUCTIONS

Install required software:

Docker Desktop

Python 3.10 or newer

Node.js 20 or newer

Git

Restart the computer after installing Docker Desktop.

Clone the project:

git clone https://github.com/
<username>/multimedijaProjekt.git
cd multimedijaProjekt

Start Elasticsearch and Kibana (required for the backend):

Open Docker Desktop and wait until it shows “Docker is running”.

In the project root directory run:

docker-compose up -d

Verify the containers are running:

docker ps

You should see two containers: "es" and "kibana".
If Elasticsearch is not running, the backend will not work.

Backend setup (Flask API):

cd backend

Create a virtual environment:

python -m venv venv

Activate it (Windows):

venv\Scripts\activate

Install dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt

Start the backend:

python app.py

The backend will run on http://localhost:5000

Available API endpoints:

/api/load (loads test data)

/api/region/<name>

/api/score (POST request)

There is no route at "/", so http://localhost:5000/
 will show 404.

Frontend setup (React + Vite):

cd ../frontend
npm install
npm run dev

The frontend runs on http://localhost:5173

Project structure:

multimedijaProjekt/
backend/ (Flask API)
frontend/ (React frontend)
docker-compose.yml (Elasticsearch + Kibana setup)

How components interact:

The frontend communicates with the backend using HTTP requests.

The backend retrieves and stores data in Elasticsearch.

Elasticsearch acts as the database for region data.

How to run the whole project (every time):

Start Docker Desktop.

In project root: docker-compose up -d

Start backend:
cd backend
venv\Scripts\activate
python app.py

Start frontend:
cd frontend
npm run dev

Open http://localhost:5173 in the browser.
